It is not just a café or a club. We offer various exhibitions, experimental art and culture events on a regular basis. The undeniably artistic atmosphere and the free-spirited public of the café will contribute to a truly bohemian entertainment. Kaņepes Culture Centre also has its own garden, which is a perfect hang-out place for warm summer nights and not just. The building that houses Kaņepes Culture Centre is over 100 years old. It was a venue for social events organized by Baltic German and Russian aristocrats, and a bohemian place during the time of the independent Latvian state, when it was occupied by students of the Art Academy. For some time the building was left uncared for, but now Kaņepes Culture Centre is restoring it room by room to bring the soul of this beautiful building back.

description: The Kremwerk - Timbre Room Complex is a queer-centric nightclub and live music venue, specializing in progressive electronic music and queer culture. The small basement space on Minor Avenue has been open only since February, but it's already establishing itself as a crucial cog in the city's electronic-music scene. Kremwerk hit the ground running. In its first week, Austin--the venue's booker--scored future-bass star L-Vis 1990, and since then, he's brought in an excellent array of local and international talent, including Silent Servant, Santiago Salazar, Dreamweapon, Jimi Jaxon, Kode 9 and Raica. Now with a capacity of 231 with its newly installed patio, we help champion the scene's underground action. Kremwerk's interior fuses an industrial, bunkerlike atmosphere (exposed, rusted pipes and sprinkler, much concrete, steel, and wood, etc.) with a chic after-hours spot. It's dimly lit and low-ceilinged and sports excellent feng shui, with plenty of nooks and seating away from the dance floor. Several shellacked and sanded tree stumps serve as tables.

name: The Fire
description: The Fire began in 1999 when Karen Lauria Saillant, opera singer, vocal coach & director, took one of the 2 pool tables out of the pool room of The Philadelphia Bar & Grille, her husband's shot & beer bar, (when he became severely handicapped due to an altercation in front of their home in center city, where he had saved her & her son from an attack) & replaced it with a tiny stage where she brought her singing students who were not opera singers to perform. Karen was left running their family tavern by herself while she & her sons also cared for her husband at home in a coma. By 2001, The Fire had become a pioneering new rock club in the Northern Liberties section of Philadelphia. Today The Fire is the oldest original music venue in Philly & a part of one of the most thriving music scenes on the East Coast. The Fire is also Philly's only female owned original music venue. The Fire is an artist-friendly venue with a passion for developing new talent, both local & touring. The Fire will soon be organizing tours for Philly's top talent in Italy. The Fire stage has hosted many artists on their rise to stardom: John Legend, My Chemical Romance, Maroon 5, Jason Mraz, OK GO, Iron and Wine, Amos Lee, Cold War Kids, Rilo Kiley, Tegan and Sara, Bill Kreutzmann (Grateful Dead), Santigold, Damien Rice, Dr. Dog, Mutlu, Schoolly D & many more. The Fire is proud to host a very diverse calendar, with Monday as the longest running & most passionately supportive open mic location in Philly. With 8 regular shows a week, The Fire features rock, folk, country, indie rock, punk, goth, hip-hop, heavy metal, dance parties and everything in between. Most shows we host are 21+ with an occasional All Ages Show and more frequent Family Friendly Shows. The Fire, now celebrating its 22nd year, is a warm, fun & friendly place to be. It is THE place in Philly to catch musicians on their way to stardom. Stop in! We look forward to meeting you!

name: Nectar Lounge
description: Handmade in 2004, Nectar Lounge is Seattle’s largest indoor/outdoor music venue. Our goal is to bring all genres to our stage and all sorts of people together in our space. Located in Seattle’s Fremont neighborhood (aka the Center of the Universe), Nectar is proud to provide a home-away-from-home where all are welcome to dance and enjoy incredible music, the one language we all speak. Nectar is the only venue of its kind in Seattle, one that showcases artists not only from all genres, but from all corners of the world. We take a global approach to music and to our space to ensure that every sound is heard and everyone feels like they’ve found their “third place” in Seattle when they come to Nectar. Our space features three full-service bars, an upstairs mezzanine with ample seating that overlooks our stage, a main floor in close proximity to the performers and a covered outdoor patio with stage views. We bring national and local musicians spanning every genre to our stage, including artists that play world music, folk, bluegrass, reggae, Americana, funk, jam, hip-hop, Latin, electronic, DJ/dance and more. We are proud to have hosted many great artists, including Pretty Lights, Anderson. Paak, Macklemore, Chromeo, The Presidents of the United States of America, Bassnectar, Greensky Bluegrass, Wiz Khalifa, Bon Iver, Allen Stone, Phosphorescent, New Mastersounds, Third World, Janelle Monae, Sir Mix-A-Lot, The Head and the Heart, Anuhea, Reggie Watts, Garage A Trois, Collie Buddz, Brandi Carlile, Barrington Levy, Sebastian Bach, The Motet, People Under the Stairs, Pharcyde, The Wailers, Chali 2Na, Bernie Worrell, Critters Buggin’, Talib Kweli, Turkuaz, Marchfourth, Aloe Blacc, Two Door Cinema Club and many more.  With our lush patio, decor and craft cocktail menu, Nectar offers a vacation escape right here in Seattle, while also making our patrons feel right at home. Come enjoy Live Music in the Center of the Universe.
